    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/questions-about-sap-websites/polluted-by-many-questions-not-about-sap-websites-in-community-2024/qaq-p/13993357</id>
    <title>Polluted by many questions NOT about SAP Websites in Community 2024</title>
    <updated>2025-01-22T15:20:25.208000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Sandra_Rossi</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/145194</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;There are two big issues in the Q&amp;amp;A of Community 2024: people using the button "Answer" (means "give solution") to just comment without giving a solution (the issue was addressed, let's see if that improves), and the other one is:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Half of my inbox is polluted by people asking a non-SAP-Websites question in the group "Question about SAP Websites".&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The reason is clear for me, they don't know where to post their SAP question, even if they search, they don't find the right group:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;The top menu contains "Products and Technology &amp;gt; Questions about SAP Websites", they choose it because they don't see a group corresponding to their question and because it contains the word "SAP" (lazy solution of course).&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;The top level "&lt;A href="https://community.sap.com/t5/forums/postpage/" target="_self"&gt;Create a post&lt;/A&gt;" is missing a search field, so they can't find easily, and they choose the easiest choice "Questions about SAP Websites".&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Sandra_Rossi_0-1737554844420.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/215515i3744B7F702F6E713/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="Sandra_Rossi_0-1737554844420.png" alt="Sandra_Rossi_0-1737554844420.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Even if a search field existed, make sure to extend the search to the group description, e.g. there's no group "sap business one", the right group is &lt;A href="https://community.sap.com/t5/enterprise-resource-planning-q-a/qa-p/erp-questions" target="_self"&gt;ERP Q&amp;amp;A&lt;/A&gt; ("SAP Business One" is in the group description):&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Sandra_Rossi_1-1737555145999.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/215516i01A7D269F9D965B6/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="Sandra_Rossi_1-1737555145999.png" alt="Sandra_Rossi_1-1737555145999.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;The six first months, I did tell the Original Poster that the question was posted to the wrong group, then I decided to alert the moderator to move the question to the right group.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;No idea what's the best solution.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Is that in the list of planned enhancements? If not, could you add it?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Thank you.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Sandra&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/questions-about-sap-websites/polluted-by-many-questions-not-about-sap-websites-in-community-2024/qaq-p/13993357"/>
    <published>2025-01-22T15:20:25.208000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
